<taxonomicName LSID="A147D389-F838-5614-9B40-3844E7BE46F9" authority="Amaral, 1921" authorityName="Amaral" authorityYear="1921" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Helicops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helicops gomesi" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gomesi">Helicops gomesi Amaral, 1921</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amaral" authorityYear="1921" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Helicops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helicops gomesi" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gomesi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Helicops gomesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all its congeners, except 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having subcaudal keels, no intergenials, and 19 dorsal scale rows throughout its body (compared to 21-24/21-22/17-19 in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. apiaka" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="apiaka">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. apiaka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs in having 125-132 ventrals in males and 128-132 in females (versus 103-119 in males and 104-125 in females of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="angulatus">H. angulatus</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
; (for information on references, see Suppl. material 3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
The distribution of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. gomesi" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="gomesi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. gomesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
extends from the Brazilian Province Sao Paulo to the Provinces Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul and Goias (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6767166" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">1</figureCitation>
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6767176" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
